nd-somalia-to-talk-to-solve-dispute%2Farticleshow%2F107031103.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107031103.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EUnited%20Nations%20Secretary%20General%20Antonio%20Guterres%20on%20Sunday%20urged%20Addis%20Ababa%20and%20Mogadishu%20to%20open%20dialogue%20to%20settle%20their%20dispute%20over%20Ethiopia's%20maritime%20deal%20with%20the%20breakaway%20region%20of%20Somaliland.%20Tensions%20in%20the%20Horn%20of%20Africa%20have%20escalated%20since%20landlocked%20Ethiopia%20struck%20a%20deal%20with%20Somaliland%20on%20January%201%20that%20gives%20it%20much%20sought-after%20access%20to%20the%20sea.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fun-urges-ethiopia-and-somalia-to-talk-to-solve-dispute%2Farticleshow%2F107031103.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fun-urges-ethiopia-and-somalia-to-talk-to-solve-dispute%2Famp_articleshow%2F107031103.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fun-urges-ethiopia-and-somalia-to-talk-to-solve-dispute%2Famp_articleshow%2F107031103.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ayodhya%3A%20The%20Sordid%20Timeline%20Leading%20to%20the%20Ram%20Temple%20Consecration%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F21161831%2FScreenshot-2024-01-21-at-4.18.07-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20January%2017%2C%202024%2C%20around%20500%20women%20took%20out%20a%20ritualistic%20procession%20termed%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EJal%20Kalash%20Yatra%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20from%20the%20banks%20of%20the%20Sarayu%20river%20in%20Ayodhya%20to%20the%20outer%20premises%20of%20the%20new%20Ram%20temple%20that%20is%20to%20be%20consecrated%20under%20the%20auspices%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20on%20January%2022.%20It%20was%20a%20spectacular%20affair%20with%20women%20in%20colourful%20dresses%20dancing%20through%20the%20streets%20of%20Ayodhya%20to%20Ram%20%3Cem%3Ebhajans%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Ekeerthans%3C%2Fem%3E%20being%20played%20out%20through%20loudspeaker%20mounted%20vehicles.%20A%20large%20number%20of%20women%20in%20the%20procession%20were%20carrying%20urns%20filled%20with%20water%20from%20the%20Sarayu%2C%20which%20was%20to%20be%20used%20for%20%E2%80%9Critualistic%20cleaning%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20premises%20of%20the%20new%20Ram%20temple.%20The%20yatra%20was%20led%20by%20Ramalakshmi%20Tripathi%2C%20wife%20of%20the%20mayor%20of%20the%20Ayodhya%20Municipality%2C%20Girish%20Pati%20Tripathi.%20Namrata%20Pathak%2C%20wife%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20Brajesh%20Pathak%20also%20participated%20in%20the%20yatra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20procession%20proceeded%20through%20the%20streets%20of%20Ayodhya%2C%20many%20old%20timers%20of%20the%20temple%20town%2C%20including%20those%20associated%20with%20%3Cem%3EJan%20Morcha%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20legendary%20people%20oriented%20newspaper%20published%20since%201958%20from%20Faizabad%2C%20Ayodhya%E2%80%99s%20twin%20town%20located%20nearly%208%20kilometres%20away%2C%20remembered%20yet%20another%20yatra%20carried%20out%20by%20the%20Viswa%20Hindu%20Parishad%20(VHP)%20nearly%20four%20decades%20ago.%20That%20was%20the%20Ram-Janaki%20rath%20yatra%2C%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%20led%20Sangh%20parivar%E2%80%99s%20first%20Ram%20temple%20based%20manoeuver%20in%20the%201980s.%20The%20Ram-Janaki%20rath%20yatra%20had%20originally%20begun%20in%20October%201984%2C%20but%20was%20called%20off%20following%20the%20assassination%20of%20then%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20on%20October%2031%2C%201984.%20In%20the%20general%20elections%20that%20followed%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%2C%20the%20Sangh%20parivar%E2%80%99s%20political%20arm%2C%20was%20routed%20and%20ended%20up%20with%20just%20two%20seats%20out%20of%20a%20total%20of%20543%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F07%2F19130137%2Fadmin-ajax-1.v1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F07%2F19130137%2Fadmin-ajax-1.v1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F07%2F19130137%2Fadmin-ajax-1.v1-300x205.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F07%2F19130137%2Fadmin-ajax-1.v1-1024x699.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-381392%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22819%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20demolition%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%201992.%20Photo%3A%20Sanjay%20Sharma%2FINDIAPIX%20NETWORK%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20in%20this%20context%2C%20in%201985%2C%20that%20the%20Sangh%20parivar%20decided%20to%20revive%20the%20Ram-Janaki%20rath%20yatra.%20The%20yatra%20was%20led%20by%20VHP%20leader%20Ashok%20Singhal%20and%20it%20had%20started%20from%20Sitamarhi%20in%20Bihar%2C%20supposedly%20the%20birth%20place%20of%20Sita%2C%20with%20the%20proclamation%20that%20the%20yatra%20would%20set%20off%20a%20series%20of%20agitations%20to%20%E2%80%9Cliberate%E2%80%9D%20the%20Ayodhya%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi.%20The%20main%20function%20related%20to%20the%20yatra%20in%20Ayodhya%20itself%20was%20to%20assemble%20before%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20and%20take%20a%20pledge%20to%20%E2%80%9Cliberate%20the%20structure%20from%20the%20clutches%20of%20the%20invaders%E2%80%9C.%20However%2C%20this%20much%20touted%20plan%20did%20not%20take%20off.%20Singhal%20and%20company%20were%20forced%20to%20beat%20a%20hasty%20retreat%20as%20a%20large%20number%20of%20Ayodhya%20residents%2C%20hailing%20from%20all%20communities%20%E2%80%93%20Hindu%2C%20Muslim%2C%20Sikh%20and%20Jain%20%E2%80%93%20got%20ready%20to%20physically%20prevent%20the%20yatra%20in%20the%20approach%20road%20to%20the%20Babri%20Masjid.%20Finally%2C%20the%20VHP%20team%20were%20forced%20to%20move%20to%20the%20banks%20of%20the%20Sarayu%2C%20close%20to%20a%20kilometre%20and%20a%20half%20from%20where%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20stood%20and%20utter%20their%20pledges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20septuagenarian%20Kabir-panthi%20follower%20based%20in%20Ayodhya%2C%20who%20wishes%20to%20call%20himself%20as%20Udhaar%20Das%20(not%20his%20real%20name)%20had%20witnessed%20both%20the%20Ram-Janaki%20rath%20yatra%20of%201985%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98Jal%20Kalash%20Yatra%E2%80%99%20of%202024.%20In%20his%20view%2C%20the%20two%20yatras%2C%20separated%20by%2040%20long%20years%20and%20hundreds%20of%20happenings%2C%20including%20extremely%20tumultuous%20ones%2C%20can%20only%20be%20seen%20as%20contrasting%20metaphors%20signifying%20two%20starkly%20different%20characteristics%20of%20the%20temple%20town%20and%20its%20adjacent%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgender%2Fwhat-happens-in-ayodhya-doesnt-stay-in-ayodhya%5C%22%3EWhat%20Happens%20in%20Ayodhya%20Doesn%E2%80%99t%20Stay%20in%20Ayodhya%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20first%20incident%20represented%20a%20spirited%20secular%20resistance%20by%20people%20from%20all%20walks%20of%20life%20against%20a%20sectarian%20communal%20movement.%20The%20second%20and%20recent%20event%20marks%20the%20surrender%20of%20this%20resistance%20and%20the%20celebration%20of%20a%20sectarian%20victory.%20%E2%80%9C%20Udhaar%20Das%20has%20been%20an%20on%20and%20off%20resident%20of%20Ayodhya%20over%20the%20past%20fifty%20years%20and%20he%20describes%20the%20change%20in%20the%20social%2C%20political%20and%20cultural%20facets%20of%20the%20temple%20town%20in%20these%20five%20decades%20as%20nothing%20short%20of%20world%20turning%20topsy-turvy.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20this%20world%20got%20overturned%20essentially%20on%20account%20of%20relentless%20attacks%20engineered%20by%20the%20Sangh%20parivar%20on%20this%20town%20and%20its%20culture.%20Those%20were%20relentless%20waves%20of%20attacks%2C%20which%20seem%20to%20have%20resulted%20in%20a%20strong%20hegemony.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20Udhaar%20Das%20was%20speaking%20with%20Kabir-panthi%2C%20Sufi%20like%20insight.%20But%20many%20years%20ago%2C%2031%20years%20ago%20to%20be%20exact%2C%20another%20self-professed%20spiritual%20practitioner%20had%20also%20spoken%20to%20me%20in%20a%20similar%20vein%2C%20albeit%20from%20a%20different%20perspective.%20That%20perspective%20was%20of%20the%20Hindutva%20warrior%20%3Cem%3Esanyasi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20the%20man%20who%20waxed%20eloquent%20on%20this%20was%20Mahant%20Ramachandra%20Paramhans%2C%20the%20then%20president%20of%20the%20Sri%20Ramajanmabhumi%20Nyas%20%E2%80%93%20a%20Trust%20set%20up%20by%20the%20Viswa%20Hindu%20Parishad%20(VHP)%20in%20the%20early%201990s%20to%20take%20the%20work%20of%20the%20Ram%20templs%20forward.%20His%20reference%20to%20waves%20of%20action%20(not%20attacks%20or%20assault%20as%20classified%20by%20Udhaar%20Das)%20was%20qualitatively%20different%20from%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20Kabir-panthi%20Sufi%20practitioner%20had%20perceived%20the%20Ayodhya%20project%20of%20the%20Sangh%20parivar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Flooking-into-ayodhyas-ongoing-statue-politics%5C%22%3ELooking%20Into%20Ayodhya%E2%80%99s%20Ongoing%20Statue%20Politics%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParamhans%20had%20spoken%20on%20the%20Hindutva%20project%20to%20me%20on%20December%206%2C1993%2C%20exactly%20one%20year%20after%20the%20demolition%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20and%20his%20treatise%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9CHindutva%20action%20waves%E2%80%9D%20went%20as%20follows.%20%E2%80%9COur%20Hindu%20Rashtra%20mission%20in%20Ayodhya%20and%20in%20Bharath%20as%20a%20whole%20is%20very%20similar%20to%20the%20waves%20in%20the%20sea.%20The%20size%2C%20the%20force%20and%20the%20intensity%20of%20the%20sea%20waves%20vary%20from%20time%20to%20time%2C%20but%20they%20never%20stop.%20It%20may%20look%20static%2C%20at%20times%20for%20the%20casual%20viewer%2C%20but%20the%20waves%20are%20moving%20and%20building%20up%20underneath%2C%20ready%20to%20strike%20big%20at%20the%20next%20opportune%20moment.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20our%20mission%20and%20the%20work%20related%20to%20it%20never%20stop.%20%3Cem%3EKaam%20jaari%20hai.%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(Work%20is%20on).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParamhans%20was%20practically%20the%20face%20of%20the%20Sangh%20Parivar%E2%80%99s%20Ayodhya%20agitation%20in%20the%20name%20of%20the%20Ram%20temple%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20along%20with%20other%20Hindutva%20hard-liner%20leaders%20like%20Ashok%20Singhal%20of%20the%20VHP%20and%20Vinay%20Katiyar%20of%20the%20Bajrang%20Dal.%20Paramhans%20was%20also%20known%20for%20resorting%20to%20rhetorical%20speeches%20and%20figurative%20expressions%20every%20now%20and%20then%2C%20but%20the%20exposition%20in%20December%201993%20on%20the%20sustained%20and%20relentless%20nature%20of%20the%20Hindutva%20campaign%20was%20made%20in%20a%20special%20and%20specific%20context.%20Barely%20two%20days%20before%20I%20met%20Paramhans%2C%20on%20December%204%2C%201993%2C%20a%20coalition%20of%20the%20Mulayam%20Singh%20Yadav-led%20Samajwadi%20Party%20(SP)%20and%20Kanshi%20Ram-led%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%20(BSP)%20had%20formed%20the%20ministry%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20with%20the%20support%20of%20the%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ascent%20of%20this%20new%20government%20was%20preceded%20by%20the%20unexpected%20defeat%20of%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20assembly%20elections%20to%20the%20state.%20This%20was%20indeed%20a%20shock%20defeat%20because%20the%20expectations%20within%20the%20Sangh%20parivar%20after%20the%20violent%20demolition%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20on%20December%206%2C%201992%20was%20that%20Hindutva%20communal%20polarisation%20has%20reached%20a%20new%20high%2C%20especially%20in%20North%20India%2C%20and%20it%20would%20consequently%20lead%20the%20BJP%20to%20easy%20and%20massive%20electoral%20wins%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15112516%2Fimg_2622-2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15112516%2Fimg_2622-2.jpg%201080w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15112516%2Fimg_2622-2-300x120.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15112516%2Fimg_2622-2-1024x410.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668157%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22432%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20the%20belief%20within%20the%20Sangh%20parivar%20was%20that%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20pan-Hindu%20social%20and%20political%20identity%20for%20which%20it%20had%20worked%20for%20decades%20has%20become%20a%20reality%2C%20at%20least%20in%20large%20parts%20of%20North%20India.%20But%20the%20social%20combination%20of%20Dalits%2C%20Other%20Backward%20Castes%20(OBC)%20and%20Muslim%20minorities%20forged%20by%20the%20BSP-SP%20alliance%20upset%20these%20hopes.%20It%20was%20in%20the%20context%20of%20this%20stunning%20electoral%20reverse%20that%20Paramhans%20spoke%20about%20the%20%E2%80%9CKaam%20Jaari%20Hai%E2%80%9D%20concept%20to%20underscore%20that%20despite%20this%20setback%20the%20Sangh%20parivar%E2%80%99s%20project%20would%20continue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20couple%20of%20days%20later%2C%20Acharya%20Giriraja%20Kishore%2C%20yet%20another%20senior%20leader%20of%20the%20VHP%2C%20joined%20Paramhans%20and%20addressed%20a%20group%20of%20reporters%20including%20self%20to%20elaborate%20what%20they%20meant%20by%20the%20%E2%80%9CKaam%20Jaari%20Hai%E2%80%9D%20idea.%20According%20to%20the%20two%20senior%20leaders%2C%20despite%20the%20electoral%20reverse%20in%20the%201993%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20assembly%20elections%2C%20the%20Hindutva%20combine%20had%20a%20dominant%20operational%20control%20over%20the%20town%20of%20Ayodhya%20and%20adjoining%20villages.%20They%20argued%20that%20the%20very%20act%20of%20removing%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%2C%20termed%20by%20both%20of%20them%20as%20%E2%80%9C%20a%20450-year-old%20blot%20on%20the%20face%20of%20India%E2%80%9D%20signified%20this%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParamhans%20and%20Kishore%20went%20on%20to%20add%20that%20the%20Sangh%20parivar%20was%20able%20to%20achieve%20this%20dominance%20not%20through%20an%20overnight%20manoeuver%20but%20as%20a%20result%20of%20sustained%20national%20and%20international%20operations%20lasting%20several%20decades.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20that%20process%2C%20there%20were%20periods%20that%20marked%20big%20and%20small%20successes%20as%20well%20as%20massive%20and%20limited%20setbacks.%20The%20appearance%20of%20the%20idol%20of%20Ram%20Lalla%20inside%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%201949%20was%20a%20major%20success.%20The%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20people%20of%20Ayodhya%20resisted%20and%20rejected%20the%20%E2%80%98Ram-Janaki%20yatra%E2%80%99%2C%20one%20of%20the%20first%20major%20exercises%20to%20propagate%20the%20liberation%20of%20Ram%20%3Cem%3Ejanmabhumi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%201985%20was%20a%20major%20setback.%20The%201986%20opening%20of%20the%20locks%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20by%20the%20then%20Rajiv%20Gandhi-led%20Congress%20government%20at%20the%20Union%20was%20a%20minor%20success%20that%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20future%20operations%20including%20%3Cem%3Ekarsevas%3C%2Fem%3E.%20But%2C%20the%20firing%20on%20the%20first%20karseva%20in%20Ayodhya%20on%20November%201990%20by%20the%20then%20Mulayam%20Singh%20Yadav%20led%20government%20was%20a%20minor%20setback%2C%20which%20highlighted%20the%20Ram%20janmabhumi%20issue%20globally%2C%20though%20it%20was%20thwarted%20locally.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20forced%20postponement%20of%20the%20July%201992%20karseva%20was%20also%20a%20minor%20reversal%20while%20the%20ultimate%20demolition%20of%20the%20Babri%20masjid%20in%20December%201992%20was%20massive%20success%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kishore%20explained%20that%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EWatch%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-its-divided-not-united-india-shankaracharya-of-jyotish-peeth-on-ayodhya-ram-temple%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98It%E2%80%99s%20Divided%2C%20Not%20United%20India%E2%80%99%3A%20Shankaracharya%20of%20Jyotish%20Peeth%20on%20Ayodhya%20Ram%20Temple%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParamhans%20added%20that%20day%20as%20follows%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20the%20VHP%20first%20started%20focussing%20on%20Ayodhya%20as%20an%20important%20organisational%20destination%2C%20Ayodhya%20was%20projected%20as%20a%20twin%20town%20of%20Faizabad%20and%20its%20hallmark%20was%20so-called%20secularism.%20But%20we%20have%20changed%20that%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20two%20decades.%20Sometimes%20through%20the%20method%20of%20step-by-step%20functioning%20and%20sometimes%20employing%20a%20flurry%20of%20fast-forward%20movements.%20These%20included%20enhancing%20our%20geographical%20space%20in%20the%20town%20by%20bringing%20more%20and%20more%20religious%20institutions%20under%20our%20banner%2C%20either%20by%20buying%20their%20property%20or%20by%20persuading%20them%20to%20ally%20with%20us.%20There%20were%20also%20mobilisations%2C%20campaigns%2C%20kar%20sevas%2C%20and%20finally%20the%20demolition.%20But%20this%20is%20work%20in%20progress.%20The%20identity%20and%20supremacy%20have%20to%20be%20strengthened%20further%20and%20we%20are%20working%20on%20that.%20In%20fact%2C%20before%20reaching%20this%20point%20of%20success%2C%20too%2C%20we%20have%20gone%20through%20several%20operational%20levels%20characterised%20by%20success%2C%20partial%20successes%2C%20partial%20failures%20and%20major%20reverses.%20But%20the%20net%20result%20is%20that%20the%20project%20has%20moved%20on.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20this%20interaction%2C%20C.K.%20Mishra%20and%20K.P.%20Singhdeo%2C%20two%20senior%20journalists%20based%20for%20long%20in%20Faizabad%2C%20recounted%20to%20me%20the%20happenings%20that%20took%20place%20in%20Ayodhya%20between%201984%20and%201992%2C%20and%20how%20these%20developments%20had%20resulted%20in%20the%20control%20and%20dominance%20that%20Paramhans%20and%20Kishore%20were%20talking%20about.%20After%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20Ram-janki%20yatra%2C%20the%20Sangh%20Parivar%20deputed%20the%20VHP%20to%20work%20in%20Ayodhya%20in%20a%20concentrated%20manner.%20Through%20many%20operations%20that%20involved%20the%20%E2%80%9CChanakya%20Neethi%20of%20%3Cem%3ESama-Dhana-Bhed-Dand%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20combination%20of%20sedate%20entreaties%2C%20distribution%20of%20largesse%2C%20blatantly%20deceitful%20manoeuvres%20and%20physical%20attacks%20on%20people%20and%20institutions%20not%20just%20in%20the%20temple%20town%2C%20but%20in%20many%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20country%2C%20the%20Sangh%20Parivar%20was%20able%20to%20take%20control%20of%20large%20physical%20tracts%20of%20Ayodhya.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20included%20big%20properties%20and%20institutions%20owned%20by%20individuals%20and%20groups%20as%20well%20as%20the%20smaller%20temples%20of%20Ayodhya%20running%20into%20hundreds.%20Those%20who%20accepted%20entreaties%20or%20accepted%20the%20largesse%20offered%20by%20the%20Sangh%20parivar%20became%20part%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpeaceful%20transition%E2%80%9C%20group.%20Those%20who%20had%20to%20be%20threatened%20or%20had%20to%20be%20physically%20dealt%20with%20formed%20the%20part%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cforceful%20takeover%E2%80%9D%20group.%20Along%20with%20all%20these%2C%20manifold%20political%20manoeuvres%2C%20marked%20by%20systematic%20spreading%20of%20misinformation%20and%20virulent%20campaigns%20with%20the%20objective%20of%20aggravating%20communal%20polarisation%2C%20came%20up%20as%20part%20of%20this%20operation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheaidem.com%2Fayodhya-the-sordid-timeline-to-the-consecration-of-ram-temple-part-one%2F%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheaidem.com%2F%5C%22%3EAIDEM%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705838715000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F21161831%2FScreenshot-2024-01-21-at-4.18.07-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fayodhya-the-sordid-timeline-leading-to-the-ram-temple-consecration%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Ram-Janaki%20rath%20yatra%20had%20originally%20begun%20in%20October%201984%2C%20but%20was%20called%20off%20following%20the%20assassination%20of%20then%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi.%20The%20second%20attempt%20was%20thwarted%20by%20a%20large%20number%20of%20Ayodhya%20residents%2C%20hailing%20from%20all%20communities%20%E2%80%93%20Hindu%2C%20Muslim%2C%20Sikh%20and%20Jain.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fayodhya-the-sordid-timeline-leading-to-the-ram-temple-consecration%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ram%20temple%20consecration%3A%20Voda%20Idea%20enhances%20network%20capacity%20in%20Ayodhya%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705837992000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2024-01%2F21%2Ffull%2F1705818799-0453.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fww