20in%20such%20earlier%20plays%20as%C2%A0%3Cem%3EHayavadana%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Cem%3EBali%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20but%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3EAgni%20Mattu%20Male%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0the%20duality%20is%20expressed%20for%20the%20first%20time%20as%20the%20explicit%20opposition%20between%20brahmin%20and%20shudra%2C%E2%80%9D%20Aparna%20Dharwadker%20observes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20Anmol%20Tikoo%20again%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20%3Cem%3EFire%20and%20the%20Rain%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20he%20creates%20this%20intricate%20structure%2C%20including%20a%20play%20within%20the%20play%2C%20that%20allows%20us%20to%20look%20beyond%20the%20elites%20and%20their%20obsessions.%20This%20is%20the%20fire%20versus%20the%20rain%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Agni%20of%20the%20dominant%20castes%20and%20their%20scriptures%2C%20versus%20the%20Male%20of%20ordinary%20folks%2C%20their%20art%20and%20their%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Mahabharata%20is%20about%20the%20difficulty%20of%20being%20good%2C%20then%C2%A0%3Cem%3EFire%20and%20the%20Rain%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0gives%20a%20positive%20counter%20to%20that%20in%20the%20transgressive%20love%20of%20Arvasu%20and%20Nittilai.%20Caring%20for%20others%2C%20those%20who%20aren%E2%80%99t%20akin%20to%20us%2C%20is%20what%20keeps%20the%20world%20going%20and%20that%20is%20what%20turns%20out%20to%20be%20the%20natural%20order%20of%20things.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EListen%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbangaloreinternationalcentre.org%2Faudio%2F182-girishkarnad8-9-the-river-has-no-fear-of-memories-being-an-existentialist%2F%5C%22%3Eepisode%208%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20River%20Has%20No%20Fear%20of%20Memories%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20where%20Karnad%20speaks%20to%20Tikoo%20and%20Arshia%20Sattar%20about%20the%20Mahabharata%2C%20history%2C%20and%20much%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Fire%20and%20the%20Rain%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0evoked%20a%20rare%20%E2%80%9Cintensity%20of%20responses%2C%20both%20negative%20and%20positive%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dha