rd%20with%20320%20in%20detention%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20small%20way%2C%20that%20is%20encouraging%20news.%20The%20figure%20is%20down%20from%20a%20high%20of%20363%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20troublingly%20large%20number%20remain%20locked%20up%2C%20undermining%20press%20freedom%20and%20often%2C%20human%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChina%20takes%20out%20unenviable%20top%20spot%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20top%20of%20the%20list%20sits%20China%20with%2044%20in%20detention%2C%20followed%20by%20Myanmar%20(43)%2C%20Belarus%20(28)%2C%20Russia%20(22)%2C%20and%20Vietnam%20(19).%20Israel%20and%20Iran%20share%20sixth%20place%20with%2017%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20dip%20in%20numbers%20is%20positive%2C%20the%20statistics%20expose%20a%20few%20troubling%20trends.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20well%20as%20a%20straight%20count%2C%20the%20Committee%20to%20Protect%20Journalists%20examines%20the%20charges%20the%20journalists%20are%20facing.%20The%20advocacy%20group%20found%20that%20globally%2C%20almost%20two-thirds%20are%20behind%20bars%20on%20what%20they%20broadly%20describe%20as%20%E2%80%9Canti-state%20charges%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20things%20such%20as%20espionage%2C%20terrorism%2C%20false%20news%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20governments%20have%20come%20to%20regard%20journalism%20as%20some%20sort%20of%20existential%20threat%20that%20has%20to%20be%20dealt%20with%20using%20national%20security%20legislation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20that%20may%20be%20justified.%20It%20is%20impossible%20to%20independently%20assess%20the%20legitimacy%20of%20each%20case%2C%20but%20it%20does%20point%20to%20the%20way%20governments%20increasingly%20regard%20information%20and%20the%20media%20as%20a%20part%20of%20the%20battlefield.%20That%20places%20journalists%20in%20the%20dangerous%20position%20of%20sometimes%20being%20unwitting%20combatants%20in%20often%20brutally%20violent%20struggles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fpalestine-gaza-israel-journalist-media%5C%22%3EMore%20Than%20One%20Journalist%20Per%20Day%20Is%20Dying%20In%20The%20Israel-Gaza%20Conflict.%20This%20Has%20To%20Stop%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%E2%80%99s%20top%20spot%20is%20hardly%20surprising.%20It%20has%20been%20there%20%E2%80%93%20or%20close%20to%20it%20%E2%80%93%20for%20some%20years.%20Censorship%20makes%20it%20extremely%20difficult%20to%20make%20an%20accurate%20assessment%20of%20the%20numbers%20behind%20bars%2C%20but%20since%20the%20crackdown%20on%20pro-democracy%20activists%20in%202021%2C%20journalists%20from%20Hong%20Kong%20have%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20found%20themselves%20locked%20up.%20And%20almost%20half%20of%20China%E2%80%99s%20total%20are%20Uyghurs%20from%20Xinjiang%2C%20where%20Beijing%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2Fcountries%2F2022-08-31%2F22-08-31-final-assesment.pdf%5C%22%3Ehuman%20rights%20abuses%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20its%20ongoing%20repression%20of%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20mostly%20Muslim%20ethnic%20minorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rest%20of%20the%20top%20four%20are%20also%20familiar%2C%20but%20the%20two%20biggest%20movements%20are%20unexpected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIran%20had%20been%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcpj.org%2Freports%2F2022%2F12%2Fnumber-of-jailed-journalists-spikes-to-new-global-record%2F%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DThe%2520Committee%2520to%2520Protect%2520Journalists%2Cin%2520a%2520deteriorating%2520media%2520landscape.%5C%22%3E2022%20gold%20medallist%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%2062%20journalists%20imprisoned.%20In%20the%20latest%20census%2C%20it%20dropped%20to%20sixth%20place%20with%20just%2017.%20And%20Israel%2C%20which%20previously%20had%20only%20one%20behind%20bars%2C%20has%20climbed%20to%20share%20that%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20positive%20news%20for%20Iranian%20journalists%2C%20but%20awkward%20for%20Israel%2C%20which%20repeatedly%20argues%20it%20is%20the%20only%20democracy%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20the%20only%20one%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jpost.com%2Fopinion%2Farticle-709045%23google_vignette%5C%22%3Erespects%20media%20freedom%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20also%20routinely%20points%20to%20Iran%20for%20its%20long-running%20assault%20on%20critics%20of%20the%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20journalists%20Israel%20had%20detained%20were%20all%20from%20the%20occupied%20West%20Bank%2C%20all%20Palestinian%2C%20and%20all%20arrested%20after%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20horrific%20attacks%20from%20Gaza%20on%20October%207.%20But%20we%20know%20very%20little%20about%20why%20they%20were%20detained.%20The%20journalists%E2%80%99%20relatives%20told%20the%20committee%20that%20most%20are%20under%20what%20Israel%20describes%20as%20%E2%80%9Cadministrative%20detention%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E17%20arrests%20in%20Israel%20in%20less%20than%202%20months%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20benign%20term%20%E2%80%9Cadministrative%20detention%E2%80%9D%20in%20fact%20means%20the%20journalists%20have%20been%20incarcerated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.btselem.org%2Ftopic%2Fadministrative_detention%5C%22%3Eindefinitely%2C%20without%20trial%20or%20charge%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20possible%20that%20they%20were%20somehow%20planning%20attacks%20or%20involved%20with%20extremism%20(Israel%20uses%20administrative%20detention%20to%20stop%20people%20they%20accuse%20of%20planning%20to%20commit%20a%20future%20offence)%20but%20the%20evidence%20used%20to%20justify%20the%20detention%20is%20not%20disclosed.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20even%20know%20why%20they%20were%20arrested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%E2%80%99s%20place%20near%20the%20top%20of%20the%20Committee%20to%20Protect%20Journalists%E2%80%99%20list%20exposes%20a%20difficult%20paradox.%20Media%20freedom%20is%20an%20intrinsic%20part%20of%20a%20free%20democracy.%20A%20vibrant%2C%20awkward%20and%20sometimes%20snarly%20media%20is%20a%20proven%20way%20to%20keep%20public%20debate%20alive%20and%20the%20political%20system%20healthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20often%20uncomfortable%2C%20but%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20strong%20democratic%20system%20without%20journalists%20freely%20and%20vigorously%20fulfilling%20their%20watchdog%20role.%20In%20fact%2C%20a%20good%20way%20to%20tell%20if%20a%20democracy%20is%20sliding%20is%20the%20extent%20of%20a%20government%E2%80%99s%20crackdown%20on%20the%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20to%20suggest%20equivalence%20between%20Israel%20and%20Iran.%20Israel%20remains%20a%20democracy%2C%20and%20Israeli%20media%20is%20often%20savagely%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesofisrael.com%2Fpublic-trust-in-government-scrapes-bottom-amid-criticism-for-inadequate-war-response%2F%5C%22%3Ecritical%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20its%20government%20in%20ways%20that%20would%20be%20unthinkable%20in%20Tehran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20Israel%20wants%20to%20restore%20confidence%20in%20its%20commitment%20to%20democratic%20norms%2C%20at%20the%20very%20least%20it%20will%20need%20to%20be%20transparent%20about%20the%20reasons%20for%20arresting%2017%20journalists%20in%20less%20than%20two%20months%2C%20and%20the%20evidence%20against%20them.%20And%20if%20there%20is%20no%20evidence%20they%20pose%20a%20genuine%20threat%20to%20Israeli%20security%2C%20they%20must%20be%20released%20immediately.%20%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F221411%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fpeter-greste-616885%5C%22%3EPeter%20Greste%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Professor%20of%20Journalism%20and%20Communications%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversati