d%20India%E2%80%99s%20Rail%20Travel%20Making%20it%20Comfortable%20for%20Millions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202005%20column%20for%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20historian%20Ramachandra%20Guha%20argued%20that%20since%20the%20dawn%20of%20Independence%2C%20there%20are%20only%20a%20few%20Government%20of%20India%20ministers%20who%20%E2%80%9Cshall%20be%20remembered%20for%20having%20carried%20out%20programmes%20that%20radically%20reshaped%20the%20lives%20of%20their%20people%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGuha%20listed%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F163334%2Fsardar-vallabhbhai-patel-ias-news%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESardar%20Vallabhai%20Patel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20as%20home%20minister%20between%201947%20and%201950%2C%20carried%20out%20the%20integration%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F124500%2Fsardar-patel-vp-menon-integration-princely-states-india-independence%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprincely%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthus%20altering%20the%20politics%20and%20geography%20of%20modern%20India%E2%80%9D.%20Next%2C%20he%20listed%20Manmohan%20Singh%2C%20who%20as%20finance%20minister%20between%201991%20and%201996%2C%20%E2%80%9Cdismantled%20the%20licence-permit-quota-raj%2C%20thus%20altering%20the%20economy%20and%20society%20of%20modern%20India%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Vallabhai%20Patel%20and%20Manmohan%20Singh%2C%20Guha%20listed%20the%20name%20of%20Madhu%20Dandavate%20%E2%80%94%20a%20physicist%2C%20freedom%20fighter%2C%20and%20socialist%20leader%20from%20Maharashtra%20%E2%80%94%20who%20as%20railway%20minister%20in%20the%20Janata%20Government%20between%201977%20and%201979%20%E2%80%9Cput%20two%20inches%20of%20foam%20on%20what%20passed%20for%20%E2%80%98reserved%20sleeper%20berths%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20second-class%20sections%20of%20trains%E2%80%9D.%20Although%20a%20simple%20intervention%2C%20this%20initiative%20had%20a%20profound%20influence%20on%20the%20lives%20of%20millions%20of%20ordinary%20Indians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Guha%20argued%2C%20%E2%80%9CBefore%201977%20(the%20year%20Dandavate%20became%20railway%20minister)%2C%20there%20was%20an%20enormous%20difference%20between%20the%20first-class%2C%20where%20the%20berths%20were%20padded%2C%20and%20the%20second-class%2C%20where%20they%20were%20made%20of%20hard%20and%20bare%20wood.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20were%20lucky%20enough%20to%20travel%20up%20front%2C%20you%20slept%20well%3B%20otherwise%20you%20woke%20up%20with%20a%20painful%20back%20and%20(were%20it%20winter)%20a%20cold%20in%20the%20head%20as%20well%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F229283%2Findian-railways-rare-pictures-history-first-train-india-gop94%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndian%20Railways%3C%2Fa%3E%20carries%20approximately%2023%20million%20passengers%20daily%20from%20nearly%20all%20strata%20of%20society.%20Dandavate%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20introduce%20these%20two%20inches%20of%20foam%20was%20driven%20by%20a%20desire%20to%20assist%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20poor%20in%20a%20practical%20way.%20As%20he%20once%20famously%20argued%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20I%20want%20to%20do%20is%20not%20degrade%20the%20first%20class%2C%20but%20elevate%20the%20second%20class%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20railway%20minister%20for%20those%20two%20years%2C%20those%20two%20inches%20of%20foam%20were%20put%20in%20place%20across%20the%20major%20trunk%20lines.%20The%20first%20train%20with%20these%20safer%20and%20more%20comfortable%20seats%20was%20flagged%20off%20on%2026%20December%2C%201977%2C%20between%20Mumbai%20and%20Kolkata%20(and%20back).%20Even%20though%20the%20Railway%20Board%20wanted%20to%20call%20this%20train%20the%20Eastern%20Express%2C%20Dandavate%20decided%20on%20the%20name%20Gitanjali%20Express%2C%20inspired%20by%20Rabindranath%20Tagore.%20The%20train%20even%20had%20portraits%20of%20the%20Bengali%20poet%20hung%20inside%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Guha%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%9COnce%20the%20process%20was%20begun%20it%20could%20scarcely%20be%20stopped.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20the%201980s%2C%20all%20trains%20of%20the%20Indian%20Railways%20had%20these%20padded%20berths%20in%20their%20second-class%20compartments.%20By%20now%20the%20change%20has%20helped%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20people.%20If%20a%20social%20history%20of%20the%20Indian%20Railways%20is%20ever%20written%2C%20it%20might%20be%20divided%20into%20two%20parts%2C%20these%20entitled%20%E2%80%98Life%20before%20Dandavate%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Life%20after%20Dandavate%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20this%20initiative%2C%20he%20also%20introduced%20the%20computerisation%20of%20railway%20reservations%20%E2%80%9Cto%20curb%20corruption%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cstreamline%20the%20procedures%E2%80%9D.%20As%20he%20noted%20in%20his%20Railway%20Budget%20speech%20for%201978-79%2C%20%E2%80%9CTo%20streamline%20the%20mammoth%20and%20complex%20operation%20involved%20in%20the%20matter%20of%20reservation%20of%20rail%20accommodation%20in%20trains%20and%20to%20eliminate%20malpractices%2C%20I%20am%20also%20considering%20computerisation%20of%20passenger%20reservations%20in%20the%20four%20metropolitan%20cities.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20repaired%20the%20relationship%20between%20the%20Indian%20Government%20and%20railway%20unions%20that%20had%20suffered%20during%20the%20strike%20of%201974%20and%20was%20suppressed%20by%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20Government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20man%20of%20his%20time%20and%20ahead%20of%20his%20time%2C%20Dandavate%20lived%20a%20remarkable%20life%20in%20the%20public%20eye.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FMadhu-Dandavate-Image-3-1705674442.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Madhu%20Dandavate%20Rail%20Minister%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FMadhu-Dandavate-Image-3-1705674442.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FMadhu-Dandavate-Image-3-1705674442-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FMadhu-Dandavate-Image-3-1705674442-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FMadhu-Dandavate-Image-3-1705674442-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FMadhu-Dandavate-Image-3-1705674442-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-338714%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EInspired%20by%20Gandhi%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20on%2021%20January%2C%201924%2C%20in%20Ahmednagar%2C%20Dandavate%20completed%20his%20MSc%20in%20Physics%20from%20the%20Royal%20Institute%20of%20Science%2C%20Mumbai%2C%20following%20which%20he%20went%20on%20to%20head%20the%20physics%20department%20at%20Siddhartha%20College%20of%20Arts%20and%20Sciences%2C%20Mumbai.%20His%20entry%20into%20politics%2C%20however%2C%20was%20inspired%20by%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20during%20the%20tumultuous%20Quit%20India%20Movement%20in%201942.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20young%20college%20student%2C%20I%20was%20present%20at%20the%20Gowalia%20Tank%20Maidan%20(August%20Kranti%20Maidan)%2C%20in%20Bombay%20on%20the%20morning%20of%209%20August%2C%201942%2C%20because%20it%20was%20announced%20that%20the%20national%20flag%20would%20be%20unfurled%20there%2C%E2%80%9D%20wrote%20Dandavate%20in%20his%20book%20%E2%80%98Dialogue%20with%20Life%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20previous%20two%20days%2C%20the%20All%20India%20Congress%20Committee%20(AICC)%20held%20a%20session%20at%20this%20very%20venue%20where%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F263172%2Fmahatma-gandhi-jayanti-best-quotes-inspiring-heroes-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMahatma%20Gandhi%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20issued%20the%20clarion%20call%20for%20%E2%80%98Quit%20India%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20in%20the%20Royal%20Institute%20of%20Science.%20I%20heard%20the%20speech%20delivered%20by%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20at%20the%20Congress%20session%20in%201942.%20I%20was%20in%20college%20when%20the%20call%20given%20to%20the%20people%20was%20%E2%80%98Do%20or%20Die%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20warning%20given%20to%20the%20British%20was%20%E2%80%98Quit%20India%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20wrote%20the%20Independence%20activist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMahatma%20Gandhi%20wanted%20his%20message%20to%20be%20heard%20all%20over%20the%20world%2C%20so%20he%20delivered%20his%20speech%20both%20in%20Hindi%20and%20English.%20I%20was%20present%20as%20a%20visitor%20in%20that%20session%20and%20was%20deeply%20moved%20and%20inspired%20by%20its%20proceedings%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20Gandhi%2C%20however%2C%20he%20was%20also%20deeply%20inspired%20by%20the%20ideals%20of%20the%20Congress%20Socialist%20Party.%20Its%20leaders%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20likes%20of%20Jayaprakash%20Narayan%2C%20Ram%20Manohar%20Lohia%2C%20and%20Yusuf%20Meherally%20%E2%80%94%20played%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20shaping%20his%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20Independence%2C%20these%20socialist%20leaders%20quit%20the%20parent%20Congress%20party%2C%20providing%20a%20strong%20and%20principled%20opposition%20to%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru.%20Dandavate%20followed%20their%20lead%20in%20this%20regard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESatyagraha%20for%20the%20Liberation%20of%20Goa%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Goa%20was%20freed%20from%20the%20clutches%20of%20Portuguese%20colonial%20rule%20and%20joined%20the%20Indian%20union%20only%20on%2019%20December%2C%201961%20(following%20military%20action%20by%20the%20Indian%20Army)%2C%20many%20leaders%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20likes%20of%20Dandavate%20%E2%80%94%20performed%20courageous%20acts%20of%20Satyagraha%20marked%20by%20nonviolent%20protests%20to%20put%20pressure%20on%20the%20Indian%20Government%20to%20act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20secretary%20of%20the%20Goa%20Vimochan%20Sahayak%20Samiti%20(Goa%20Liberation%20Aid%20Committee)%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20he%20bravely%20led%20a%20group%20of%2093%20people%20to%20launch%20a%20Satyagraha%20at%20Netarda%20(a%20small%20village%20on%20the%20border%20of%20Goa)%20and%20paid%20a%20pretty%20heavy%20price%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20he%20wrote%20in%20his%20book%20%E2%80%98Dialogue%20with%20Life%2C%20%E2%80%9CNormally%20when%20the%20Satyagraha%20was%20announced%2C%20the%20police%20were%20posted%20on%20the%20border%2C%20but%20we%20walked%20about%207-8%20miles%20beyond%20the%20Portuguese%20border%2C%20raising%20slogans.%20I%20had%20the%20national%20tricolour%20flag%20in%20my%20hand.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Portuguese%20police%20came.%20They%20were%20well-armed.%20We%20were%20stopped.%20I%20was%20in%20the%20front%20and%20was%20asked%20to%20hand%20over%20the%20flag.%20I%20refused%20to%20do%20so.%20We%20had%20come%20here%20to%20hoist%20this%20flag%20in%20the%20Goan%20territory%2C%20and%20I%20would%20not%20surrender%20it.%20They%20beat%20me%20and%20after%20an%20intense%20struggle%2C%20they%20took%20away%20the%20flag.%20We%20were%20asked%20to%20return%20but%20we%20did%20not%20budge%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBacked%20by%20slogans%20like%3Cem%3E%20%E2%80%98Nahin%2C%20nahin%2C%20Kabhi%20nahin%2C%20Bharat%20Goa%20alag%20nahin%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98Lathi%2C%20goli%20khayenge%2C%20phir%20bhi%20Goa%20jayenge%E2%80%99%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehe%20took%20on%20the%20might%20of%20the%20Portuguese%20colonial%20police%20as%20they%20began%20a%20lathi%20charge%20on%20all%20%3Cem%3Esatyagrahis%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20beat%20them%20with%20the%20butts%20of%20their%20rifles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20beat%20me%20till%20I%20fell%20unconscious.%20Strangely%20enough%2C%20even%20after%20I%20became%20unconscious%2C%20they%20trampled%20on%20my%20back%20with%20their%20military%20shoes.%20After%20a%20while%2C%20my%20colleagues%20took%20me%20to%20the%20Military%20Hospital%20at%20Belgaum%20and%20then%20to%20Bombay.%20They%20found%20that%20my%20hip%20joints%20were%20injured%20very%20badly%20and%20I%20had%20to%20be%20given%20infrared%20rays%20for%20that%20injury.%20My%20strong%20young%20bones%20could%20take%20the%20torture%20then%2C%20but%20later%20on%2C%20after%20many%20years%2C%20it%20was%20diagnosed%20that%20my%20hip%20joints%20had%20totally%20degenerated%20and%20the%20replacement%20of%20these%20joints%20with%20metallic%20plates%20and%20rods%20was%20the%20only%20solution.%20At%20present%20I%20have%20two%20stainless%20steel%20plates%20and%20two%20metallic%20rods%20in%20my%20body%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20really%20a%20brutal%20episode%20as%20far%20as%20police%20action%20is%20concerned.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20the%20police%20would%20usually%20just%20arrest%20the%20%3Cem%3Esatyagrahis%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20take%20them%20to%20jail.%20But%20the%20%3Cem%3Esatyagrahis%20%3C%2Fem%3Emade%20their%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWriting%20on%20the%20impact%20of%20this%20Satyagraha%20action%2C%20he%20noted%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20feel%20proud%20to%20say%20that%20it%20did%20generate%20a%20climate%20to%20pressurise%20the%20Indian%20Government%20leading%20to%20the%20military%20action%20to%20liberate%20Goa.%20There%20was%20hardly%20any%20resistance%20during%20the%20military%20action.%20My%20feeling%20is%20if%20this%20military%20action%20had%20been%20taken%20earlier%2C%20there%20would%20not%20have%20been%20so%20much%20sacrifice%20and%20death.%20Our%20Satyagraha%20in%201955%20did%20create%20a%20spirit%20of%20resistance%20against%20Portuguese%20rule%20in%20Goa.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ETaking%20on%20Indira%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20Emergency%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20many%20of%20his%20socialist%20peers%2C%20Dandavate%20challenged%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20administration%E2%80%99s%20proclamation%20of%20Emergency%20(1975%20to%201977)%20%E2%80%94%20a%20dark%20period%20in%20our%20history%20marked%20by%20the%20usurping%20of%20basic%20civil%20rights%20and%20democracy%20%E2%80%94%20and%20served%20many%20stints%20in%20prison%20as%20a%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWitnessing%20the%20inhuman%20treatment%20meted%20out%20to%20political%20prisoners%2C%20particularly%20his%20colleague%20and%20socialist%20leader%20Mrinal%20Gore%2C%20Dandavate%20shot%20off%20a%20letter%20to%20Indira%20Gandhi%20from%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20am%20quite%20conscious%20of%20the%20consequences%20of%20this%20letter.%20I%20can%20well%20imagine%20that%20through%20this%20communication%2C%20I%20am%20likely%20to%20incur%20your%20wrath%20and%20get%20my%20detention%20prolonged.%20However%2C%20I%20feel%20least%20worried%20about%20it.%20I%20will%20remain%20completely%20undeterred%20even%20if%20the%20prison%20yard%20from%20which%20I%20write%20this%20letter%20were%20to%20become%20my%20graveyard%2C%E2%80%9D%20wrote%20Madhu%20Dandavate%20in%20a%20letter%20dated%2014%20January%2C%201976%2C%20to%20the%20then%20prime%20minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20during%20the%20Emergency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20signed%20off%20this%20scathing%20letter%20to%20the%20then-prime%20minister%20by%20declaring%20his%20undying%20will%20to%20resist.%20%E2%80%9CRest%20assured%20that%20in%20this%20land%20of%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%2C%20my%20will%20to%20fight%20for%20freedom%20will%20ever%20remain%20more%20powerful%20than%20the%20engine%20of%20repression%20that%20seeks%20to%20suppress%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDandavate%2C%20however%2C%20is%20also%20famously%20known%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F214827%2Fvalentines-day-love-letters-emergency-madhu-pramila-dandavate-history-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehis%20series%20of%20letters%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20jail%20to%20his%20wife%20Pramila%2C%20a%20legendary%20socialist%20activist%20in%20her%20own%20right%2C%20who%20was%20also%20imprisoned%20during%20the%20Emergency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20nearly%2023%20years%20of%20marriage%2C%20the%20couple%20were%20suddenly%20split%20apart%20by%20a%20distance%20of%20over%20800%20km.%20As%20products%20of%20the%20freedom%20struggle%2C%20avowed%20socialists%20and%20seasoned%20activists%2C%20the%20Government%20arrested%20Dandavate%20on%2026%20June%2C%201975%2C%20and%20subsequently%20picked%20up%20Pramila%20on%2017%20July%2C%201975.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20their%20time%20in%20prison%2C%20the%20only%20way%20they%20could%20correspond%20was%20through%20letters.%20The%20couple%20exchanged%20nearly%20200%20letters%2C%20where%20they%20discussed%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20music%2C%20poetry%2C%20books%2C%20philosophy%20and%20politics.%20More%20importantly%2C%20however%2C%20their%20letters%20were%20a%20testament%20to%20how%20the%20love%20they%20shared%20for%20each%20other%20translated%20into%20resistance%20against%20an%20authoritarian%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20letters%20register%20the%20pain%20of%20separation%20as%20well%20as%20how%20they%20worked%20through%20it%20to%20reaffirm%20their%20emotional%20bond%20by%20restating%20their%20commitment%20to%20freedom%E2%80%A6.They%20loved%20each%20other%20because%20they%20loved%20freedom.%20Their%20love%20also%20enriched%20and%20extended%20the%20meaning%20of%20freedom%2C%E2%80%9D%20wrote%20scholar%20Gyan%20Prakash%20in%20%3Cem%3EEmergency%20Chronicles%3A%20Indira%20Gandhi%20and%20Democracy%E2%80%99s%20Turning%20Point%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cd